    <section id="legacy">
        <h2>Legacy</h2>
        <p>Stephen Curry's legacy is marked by his transformative impact on the game of basketball. As a two-time NBA Most Valuable
        Player (MVP) and three-time NBA champion with the Golden State Warriors, Curry's unique style of play has revolutionized
        the sport. His exceptional three-point shooting ability, often characterized as "Steph Range," has redefined the way the
        game is played, influencing an entire generation of players to prioritize long-range shooting. Curry's offensive prowess
        and ball-handling skills have not only earned him personal accolades but also elevated his team to championship heights,
        symbolizing a new era of "small ball" basketball.
        <br>
        <br>
        Beyond his on-court achievements, Curry's legacy extends to philanthropy and community engagement. He and his wife,
        Ayesha, established the Eat. Learn. Play. Foundation, focusing on childhood hunger, education, and wellness. As a
        result, Curry's impact stretches beyond the court, reflecting his commitment to making a positive difference in the
        lives of youth and underserved communities. Steph Curry's legacy is not only about changing the way basketball is played
        but also about using his platform to inspire and effect real-world change, both in the game and the communities he
        serves.</p>
        
    </section>

